'''Upland Unified School District''' is a [[school district]] located in [[San Bernardino County]], [[California]] that serves the community of [[Upland, California]]. It has a total population of approximately 63,800 and covers a total area of 24 square miles.<ref>Upland Unified School District: "UUSD Boundary"</ref>

==History==
[[Upland High School]] has been a part of the district since it left the [[Chaffey Joint Union High School District]] in 1991.

==Schools==
The Upland Unified School District is a K-12 district. It has ten [[elementary schools]], two [[junior high schools]], and two [[secondary school|high schools]]. One of the high schools is a continuation school. The district enrolled 12,285 students in 2005. All of the schools are located in Upland, California.<ref name="vvsd-schools">Upland Unified School District: "UUSD Schools"</ref>

